<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-409-481  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 409 481.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Sept 3 1990 v7 n34 p19(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Cahners-Ziff Publishing Associates LP 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Fortran compiler helps programmers add MultiFinder support.andO;(Language Systems Corp.'s Fortran 2.1) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Patch, Kimberly.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Language Systems Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Fortran 2.1 (Compiler) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionCompilersFORTRANEnhancementsProgram Development ToolsAdd-In-On Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Fortran compiler helps programmers add MultiFinder supportandM;HERNDON, Va.andP;  -- Language Systems has announced an upgrade to its Fortrancompiler that automatically gives compiled programs the ability to process inthe background under Apple Computer's Multi-Finder on a Macintosh.andM;Language Systems' Fortran version 2.1 lets users launch an applicationcompiled with the program under MultiFinder, switch the application into thebackground and use the computer for other tasks while the applicationcontinues to run.andM;According to Language Systems officials, the learning curve for writingMacintosh background applications is normally several weeks, but the upgradesidesteps this process.andP;  &quot;Language Systems' Fortran 2.1 has reduced this timeto zero,&quot; said Rich Norling, the company's chairman.andM;Language Systems' Fortran 2.1 allows for nested include files and longvariable names.andP;  It accepts 72-column or free-form source code tabbing.andP;  Italso supports conditional compilation, range checking, cross-referencingbetween symbol tables, assembler source listing and direct code generationfor all available Macintosh processors, according to officials.andM;The compiler can be used with versions 2.0.2 and later of the MacintoshProgrammers Workshop Development Environment.andP;  Language Systems' Fortransupports math libraries from IMSL and NAG, among other third-party products.andM;Language Systems' Fortran 2.1 comes bundled with the Macintosh ProgrammersWorkshop Development Environment version 3.1 and is available now.andP;  Thepackage is priced at $495; an upgrade is available free to Fortran version2.0 users.andM;Language Systems Corp. can be contacted at 441 Carlisle Drive, Herndon, VA22070, (703) 478-0181.andO;</TEXT></DOC>